{"word":"ἅλς","slug":"ἅλς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἅλς</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> SAL\n<p/><div class='li250'><b>A. </b>as <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a>, <i>a lump of salt</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: generally, <i>salt</i>, <a href='S:often'>oft.</a> in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἁλὸς μέταλλον</el> a <i>salt</i>-mine, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li250'><b>B. </b>as <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> sg., <i>the sea</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}